---

# Summary

The separation of the Request Path and Analytics Path is the defining architectural decision of the platform. User-facing requests remain lightweight and latency-sensitive, while computationally expensive analytics execute asynchronously through independent processing pipelines. This separation enables the system to scale each responsibility independently while maintaining a responsive user experience.
